Eleventh Avenue, east side, north from and including 49th Street. 682 Eleventh Avenue, at the S.E. corner of 49th Street, is Horn & Hardart's Lunch and Day-Old Bake Shop, erected in 1928. 684 Eleventh Avenue, on the N.E. corner, with the adjoining building, has just been demolished. In the block above, 708-710 Eleventh Avenue, between 50th and 51st Streets, is to be demolished in 1935. April 15, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
